column70: Any additional comments or suggestions?
People may be more inclined to purchase a plan if they are provided a free tub of popcorns with every multiplex movie of the Golden Ticket.

First, the plan is confusing: "Additional tickets, when purchased together, are discounted at 20% off" What does it mean? If I buy more than one ticket? Second, the 20% off on additional tickets is not provided in choosing pricing (just says OTT+1/2/4 free). Third, my understanding is that they are curating movies/shows that are already on OTT in that month.  This can work if the movies are released directly on OTT in India and this subscription lets me watch such movies in theatre. Otherwise, I am paying to watch a movie (say poor things) much later after its release. Fourth, a concern would be people are used to convenience/forwarding movies. Looks like the target customers for this maybe very niche who appreciate certain movies.
If only eatables can be subsidized, then maybe there would be a huge crowd pulling.
Meow Meow Meow Meow

Complementary popcorn and drink & reward points accumulated after the show + review about movie on app can increase the subscription. Target looks like the upper middle class/ high class premium urban movie goers. Challenge -Substandard movie quality. And non availability of movies (due to strike from actors end to distributors/theatre owners end)could pose a problem. Ratings of movies must not be less than 7.5 IMDb or some other yardstick must be catered. Incase no movies are available of set standard, there must be a mechanism to play the old famous movies including foreign language movies(like re-release), Oscar awards/Canne movie festival featured/national award winning movies exclusive for the golden ticket. A campaign could be held for the golden ticket holders at the end of every month/quarter all across the country to draw a lucky winner to have a coffee date with a movie star. Multiple winners can be given the offer to work in a movie set/ theatre operations/ be part of a movie vlog/ internship/partnership/networking with film industry depending on the winners profile. Exclusive seating can be considered for golden ticket holders.
There should be flexibility in Cinema options and some value-added features like cancelation or re-booking, offers/discounts on F&B etc.

I don't think I would be willing to pay extra for the OTT plan. Even if I were it would have to be a marginal amount. But given that netflix does introduce this idea I would switch over from Amazon or any other OTT to become a loyal member of Netflix.

The content quality and exclusiveness will be the key incentive for me to start going to theatres more frequently for the experience.
Also, maybe a subtle push can be done fron the OTT platform itself suggesting a new movie release at a nearby theatre and possible to be booked within the app/ott website can be nice user conversion point.

A very interesting service though

Given the busyness of my life, going to the theater might not always seem practical as I am getting older. However, if I had this Golden ticket subscription service that not only provides access to movies but also sends timely reminders like 'Your 4 free movies are about to expire this month,' it would act as a gentle nudge to motivate me to take the time and enjoy the experience. It would make the idea of going back to the theater more enticing and integrate it into my schedule, while also creating a sense of urgency to make the most out of my subscription. Well as a suggestion, if there is a platform where golden ticket subscribers can form as a community and share each other views on movie recommendations or calling out for group movie outings with strangers. I guess more people would be interested. Great job btw, all the best for your project 👍
